news.title: Diesel generators sets in colony green belt in Gurugram: NGT pulls up senior officials for 'inaction'
news.para: The tribunal was hearing a petition filed last year by Gurgaon resident Raman Sharma, who had alleged that 10 diesel generators were being run from a green belt in Malibu Town, Sector 47, and that construction and demolition waste was regularly dumped in the residential colony.

news.title: Borrowers refinance home loans as tenures go beyond retirement
news.para: While floating rates mean that borrowers have to pay the rates prevailing in the market, this may be the best time to refinance loans as lenders are willing to sacrifice some of their margins for new customers.

news.title: On 16th week of protest, Greater Noida West buyers plan to send postcards to PM
news.para: More than 60,000 homebuyers in over 20 societies are awaiting possession and registries of their flats, some for over a decade.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to upload status of 197 projects on website
news.para: The Noida Authority has recently uploaded the details of its 115 projects, including their status of completion and occupation certificates, arrears, disputes and registry of flats, on its website.

news.title: YEIDA plans scheme to collect Rs 4,450 crore from 14 builders
news.para: Officials said that of the Rs 4,457 crore that YEIDA was to collect from the builders, Rs 2,753 crore was land premium, Rs 1,408 crore additional compensation for farmers and Rs 296 crore lease rent.

news.title: Prime minister inaugurates new metro line in Bengaluru
news.para: ​Officials said this section is the eastern extension to the operational East-West Corridor (Purple Line) from Baiyappanahalli to Whitefield Station.

news.title: Enforcement directorate attaches Rs 33 crore assets of Heera Group in Hyderabad
news.para: Investigation revealed that Nowhera Shaik and her Heera Group of companies utilised part of proceeds of crime towards purchase of various immovable properties in her name and that of her companies.

news.title: Small office space hot in Kolkata market
news.para: Overall office space demand witnessed in the city grew from a little over 0.8 m sq ft in 2021 to over 1.1 m sq ft in 2022, a growth of 42% year-on-year.

news.title: IGR panel to study property registration with maps in Maharashtra
news.para: Officials said that registration with maps will make the property title more accurate. Some states have started using maps for registration of properties.

news.title: Property tax collection doubled in financial year 2022-23 in Chennai
news.para: In 2019-20, the civic body collected 928 crore, and during 2020-21, due to Covid-19, it collected 471.6 crore, a lesser collection. The corporation has urged the residents who have not paid taxes to pay immediately.

news.title: Uttar Prdesh PWD minister promises to resolve builder-buyer issues in Noida
news.para: The minister said MoUs worth Rs 35 lakh crore were signed at the UP Global Investor Summit in February 2023, of which GB Nagar’s share is Rs 9 lakh crore.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Realty price war intensifies as Nerul plot sells for Rs 6.72 lakh per sq meter
news.para: Cidco is expected to realize Rs 165.42 crore for the 2,459.33 sq mtr plot (residential-cum-commercial) which enjoys an FSI of 1 to 1.5.

news.title: Tufropes' director buys Rs 121-crore apartment in South Mumbai
news.para: The apartment spread over 9,546 sq ft is on the 19th floors of the super-luxury residential tower, Lodha Malabar, located on the plush Walkeshwar Road, opposite the governor’s estate. The under-construction tower is adjacent to the Arabian Sea and the Hanging Gardens.

news.title: Landlords raise rent on more than half of properties in England: ONS
news.para: The Office for National Statistics (ONS) analysed data collected every 12 months about privately-rented homes, revisiting the properties to track price changes over time.

news.title: China: Kaisa Group Holdings forecasts loss of up to about $2 billion
news.para: The Shenzhen-based company earlier this month, published its long-delayed results for fiscal 2021 in which it reported a loss of 13.26 billion yuan.
